I tried wrapping each binary result from the database in a class that only converted to a UUID when I called str(), but initializing all those classes ended up being even slower.

```
class LazyUUID(object):
    __slots__ = ('bytes', 'uuid')

    def __init__(self, bytes):
        self.bytes = bytes
        self.uuid = None

    def __str__(self):
        if self.uuid is None:
            self.uuid = uuid.UUID(bytes=self.bytes)
        return str(self.uuid)


class LazyUUIDType(types.TypeDecorator):
    impl = types.BINARY(16)

    def process_result_value(self, value, dialect):
        if value is None:
            return value

        return LazyUUID(bytes=value)
```

