```python
def castable(self, value):
    if isinstance(value, str):
        return self.config
    else:
        return isinstance(value, self._cast_types)

def cast(self, value):
    if isinstance(value, str) and self.config:
        return self.from_string(value)
    else:
        return super().cast(value)
```

This would mean that you could simply `setattr(obj, trait, config_value)` or use `trait.cast(config_value)` explicitly. I'm just not sure that you would want traits to always try and cast config style values.

